<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="343" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,633,910]" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,633,658]" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small hamsters with long to moderately sized tail, naked elongated feet and wavy margin of dorsal coloration. Rostrum slender and long, zygomatic plate straight. Hamular process of squamosum narrow and straight. Molars relatively narrow and high-crowned, main cusps elongated, labial and lingual anterocones (-conids) positioned close to each other, mesolophids (posterior ridges of metaconid) in m1 and m2 usually present. Auditory bullae small to medium-sized with extended tubular anterior part, stapedial foramen of normal size and position.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,633,910]" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,813,838]" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Satunin" authorityYear="1902" box="[468,601,814,837]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Urocricetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[468,601,814,837]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Urocricetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all recent cricetines other than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1910" box="[1248,1360,813,838]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phodopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1248,1360,813,838]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Phodopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of bullae tympani, which has a long tube-like protrusion on its anterior part (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1140,849,874]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[449,1136,962,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[449,1136,962,1905]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ventro-lateral view of the auditory bulla; (a) Cricetulus longicaudatus (ZMMU S-63115), (b) Urocricetus aff.alticola (ZMMU S-155360)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1187500/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1910" box="[1324,1436,849,874]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phodopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,849,874]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Phodopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by position and size of the stapedial foramen, lack of fur on palms and soles, and length of tail.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1187500/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" startId="11.[151,250,1925,1947]" targetBox="[449,1136,962,1905]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1925,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1925,1947]" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
Ventro-lateral view of the auditory bulla; (a) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[789,1050,1925,1947]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[789,1050,1925,1947]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Cricetulus longicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ZMMU S-63115), (b) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1917" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Urocricetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="342">Urocricetus aff.alticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ZMMU S-155360).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,302,151,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Content.</emphasis>
Includes at least two speciesâ€“ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Satunin" authorityYear="1902" box="[642,778,151,176]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamensis">
<emphasis box="[642,778,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">U. kamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[834,960,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1917" box="[834,956,151,176]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Urocricetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alticola">U. alticola</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the status of 
<emphasis box="[1111,1228,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">thibetanus</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonhote" authorityYear="1905" box="[1283,1339,151,176]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lama">
<emphasis box="[1283,1339,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">lama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires additional examination. Does not include 
<emphasis box="[619,706,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Satunin" authorityYear="1903" box="[619,702,188,213]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kozlovi">kozlovi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">
The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov, 2018" authorityName="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov" authorityYear="2018" box="[414,530,223,248]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="sensu lato">
<emphasis box="[414,530,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Cricetulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[538,650,223,248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also violated by the phylogenetic position of 
<emphasis box="[1188,1360,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lebedev &amp; Potapova" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1188,1356,224,248]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="migratorius">C. migratorius</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which proves to be more closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[564,659,261,284]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,659,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Cricetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[715,872,260,285]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Allocricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[715,872,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Allocricetulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov" authorityYear="2018" box="[966,1123,260,285]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barabensis">
<emphasis box="[966,1123,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. barabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[1179,1371,260,285]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[1179,1371,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. longicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This result, which was first obtained by Neumann 
<emphasis box="[687,747,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">et al.</emphasis>
(2006), is fully supported here based on a more extensive sampling. There is no evidence that this phylogenetic arrangement is an artifact of some secondary signal such as base composition bias.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">
It should be indicated that the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov" authorityYear="2018" box="[606,723,404,429]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[606,723,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Cricetulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its traditional sense (i.e. including 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lebedev &amp; Potapova" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1142,1306,405,428]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="migratorius">
<emphasis box="[1142,1306,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. migratorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) appears to be an artificial grouping of small-sized hamsters. No morphological or chromosomal synapomorphies are known to support its monophyly despite the fact that Palearctic hamsters are relatively well studied from both perspectives (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation box="[208,390,512,536]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" refId="ref8459" refString="Vorontsov, N. N. (1982) [The hamsters (Cricetidae) of the world fauna. Part I. Morphology and ecology]. Fauna of the USSR, Series Nov., No. 125, Mammals, 3 (6), 1 - 451. [in Russian]" type="journal article">Vorontsov 1982</bibRefCitation>
; Romanenko 
<emphasis box="[545,595,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">et al</emphasis>
. 2007).Thus, the grey hamster can not be retained within 
<taxonomicName authority="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov, 2018" authorityName="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov" authorityYear="2018" box="[1249,1366,511,536]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="sensu stricto">
<emphasis box="[1249,1366,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Cricetulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="12" pageNumber="343" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which should include only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lebedev &amp; Bannikova &amp; Neumann &amp; Ushakova &amp; Ivanova &amp; Surov" authorityYear="2018" box="[572,734,548,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barabensis">
<emphasis box="[572,734,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. barabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[755,805,548,572]" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">type</typeStatus>
species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Orlov and Malygin" authorityYear="1988" box="[930,1062,548,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sokolovi">
<emphasis box="[930,1062,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. sokolovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[1130,1329,548,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1329,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. longicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From a morphological viewpoint, there are no reasons to lump 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lebedev &amp; Potapova" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[844,1018,584,608]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="migratorius">
<emphasis box="[844,1018,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. migratorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its sister taxaâ€” 
<taxonomicName box="[1284,1379,584,607]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1284,1379,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Cricetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,333,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">Allocricetulusâ€”</emphasis>
into a single genus taking into account the substantial level of morphological and genetic divergence among the three branches. Therefore, the only possible decision is to assign 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lebedev &amp; Potapova" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1161,1327,656,680]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricetulus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="migratorius">
<emphasis box="[1161,1327,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="343">C. migratorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to a new genus, the description of which is given below.
</paragraph>
